#This dataset date ranges from 05/02/2010 to 26/10/2012
#There are 6435 stores
#The fuel price ranges from $2.472 to $4.468 a gallon
#Weekly sales range from $209,986.25 to $3,818,686.45
#There was 450 stores that had a holiday flag
#Temperature median was 62.67 degrees
#Unemployment percentage ranged from 3.879% to 14.313%
#Even though there were times that weekly sales, and unemployment 
#changed, there were no indication that there were directly effecting 
#each other every time
#Even though there were times when weekly sales increased and fuel 
#prices decreased, there were no indication that there were correlated or 
#effecting one another because it didn't always happen
